  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "However, after January 2022, the GPT3 version (davinci-002) solved 70% of the ToM questions, a performance comparable to that of 7 year-olds.",
    "The November 2022 version (davinci-003) solved 93% of the ToM questions, a performance comparable to that of 9 yearold children.",
    "These findings suggest that the ToM ability (so far thought to be exclusively human) may have emerged spontaneously as a by-product of improving the language skills of language models [37].In a recent study published in Nature, scientists tested two families of LLMs (GPT and LLaMA2 from Meta) repeatedly against ToM measures and compared their performance with those from a sample of 1,907 human participants.",
    "Across the battery of theory of mind tests, they found that GPT-4 models performed at, or even sometimes above, human levels at identifying indirect requests, false beliefs, and misdirection, but struggled with detecting faux pas.",
    "Faux pas is considered an advanced test of ToM ability as it requires subtle social reasoning, and it was the only test where LLaMA2 managed to outperform humans."
  ],
